1. Create an empty queue to store the nodes of the search tree.
2. Create an initial node for the search tree.
3. Add the initial node to the queue.
4. While the queue is not empty:
      a. Remove the first node from the queue.
      b. If the node represents a complete tour:
            i. Update the best tour found so far.
      c. If the node represents a partial tour and its cost is less than the cost of the best tour found so far:
            i. Generate child nodes by adding an unvisited city to the partial tour.
            ii. Add the child nodes to the queue in order of increasing cost.
5. Return the best tour found.

